i have been looking at another channel (Ants Australia) and i saw a video about Argentine ants and since i found out about them i feel like it is possible for you to keep a multi - Formicarium ant super-colony ( where you can keep an ant colony of Argentine ants and wait for them to be mature. After that, once the queens mated with the Alates', the one fertile queen or multiple fertile queens will move so you will be able to move them in another Formicarium if you want to because this is probably a bit too much since Argentine ants form super-colonies and you will have to do so more stuff since you already have a lot of ant colonies, your parrot [sorry forgot her name], your fish , and your other pets ) if you can thanks .
Also, I have learned (from the same channel) that you can scoop up a pile of workers and brood without queen and a starting colony of arginine ants with a queen mix and what happen is that they still go on with their day and make an alliance and continue to grow.
You don't have to do this, this is just some idea that you can possibly do and if you can thanks.
